---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { pageBreadcrumb, pageUrl, webPage } from '../../lib/schema';

const url = pageUrl('register');
const title = 'Sign in — Runlog';
const description =
  'Runlog uses passwordless email-link sign-in. There is no separate registration step — sign in with your email to access your account and API keys.';

const graph = [
  pageBreadcrumb({ name: 'Register', url }),
  webPage({ url, name: 'Sign in to Runlog', description }),
];
---
<Base
  title={title}
  description={description}
  canonical={url}
  dataNoNumber
  graph={graph}
>
  <h1>Registration is now sign-in</h1>
  <p>
    Runlog moved to passwordless email-link sign-in. There is no separate registration
    step — enter your email on the sign-in page and you'll receive a one-time link.
    Once signed in, you can manage your API keys from your account dashboard.
  </p>
  <p><a class="form-button" href="/login/">Sign in</a></p>

  <p lang="en">
    When you sign in, your email address is processed by the data controller (see
    <a href="/impressum/">Impressum</a>) for the sole purpose of authenticating your
    account. No use beyond authentication, no third-party sharing beyond the
    email-delivery service. Full disclosure: <a href="/datenschutz/">Privacy Notice</a>.
  </p>
  <p lang="de">
    Bei der Anmeldung wird Deine E-Mail-Adresse vom Verantwortlichen (siehe
    <a href="/impressum/">Impressum</a>) ausschließlich zur Authentifizierung Deines
    Kontos verarbeitet. Keine darüber hinausgehende Nutzung, keine Weitergabe außer
    an den E-Mail-Dienstleister.
    Vollständige Auskunft: <a href="/datenschutz/">Datenschutzerklärung</a>.
  </p>

  <p>
    Once you have a key, head to <a href="/quickstart/">Quickstart</a> for the 4-step setup
    (sign in &rarr; wire MCP &rarr; drop in the skill &rarr; use Claude normally) or browse
    <a href="/agents/">Agents</a> for the per-vendor install paths covering Claude Code,
    Cursor, Cline, Continue, Windsurf, Aider, VS Code Copilot, JetBrains AI, and Zed.
  </p>
</Base>
